90/** Define a shader permutation uniquely according to its type, and permutation id.*/
91template<typename MetaShaderType>
92struct TShaderTypePermutation
93{
94 MetaShaderType* const Type;
95 const int32 PermutationId;
96
97 TShaderTypePermutation(MetaShaderType* InType, int32 InPermutationId)
98 : Type(InType)
99 , PermutationId(InPermutationId)
100 {
101 }
102
103 FORCEINLINE bool operator==(const TShaderTypePermutation& Other)const
104 {
105 return Type == Other.Type && PermutationId == Other.PermutationId;
106 }
107
108 FORCEINLINE bool operator!=(const TShaderTypePermutation& Other)const
109 {
110 return !(*this == Other);
111 }
112
113 friend FORCEINLINE uint32 GetTypeHash(const TShaderTypePermutation& Var)
114 {
115 return HashCombine(GetTypeHash(Var.Type), (uint32)Var.PermutationId);
116 }
117};
118
119using FShaderPermutation = TShaderTypePermutation<FShaderType>;
120
121inline const int32 kUniqueShaderPermutationId = 0;
122
123/** Used to compare order shader types permutation deterministically. */
124template<typename MetaShaderType>
125class TCompareShaderTypePermutation
126{
127public:
128 FORCEINLINE bool operator()(const TShaderTypePermutation<MetaShaderType>& A, const TShaderTypePermutation<MetaShaderType>& B) const
129 {
130 int32 AL = FCString::Strlen(A.Type->GetName());
131 int32 BL = FCString::Strlen(B.Type->GetName());
132 if (AL == BL)
133 {
134 int32 StrCmp = FCString::Strncmp(A.Type->GetName(), B.Type->GetName(), AL);
135 if (StrCmp != 0)
136 {
137 return StrCmp > 0;
138 }
139 return A.PermutationId > B.PermutationId;
140 }
141 return AL > BL;
142 }
143};

399 inline FRHIShader* GetShader(int32 ShaderIndex, bool bRequired = true)
400 {
401 // This is a double checked locking. This trickery arises from the fact that we're
402 // synchronizing two threads: one that takes a lock and another that doesn't.
403 // Without fences, there is a race between storing the shader pointer and accessing it
404 // on the other (lockless) thread.
405 FRHIShader* Shader = RHIShaders[ShaderIndex].load(std::memory_order_acquire);
406 if (UNLIKELY(Shader == nullptr))
407 {
408 Shader = CreateShaderOrCrash(ShaderIndex, bRequired);
409 }
410 return Shader;
411 }

942 /** Finds an automatically bound uniform buffer matching the given uniform buffer struct if one exists, or returns an unbound parameter. */
943 FORCEINLINE_DEBUGGABLE const FShaderUniformBufferParameter& GetUniformBufferParameter(const FShaderParametersMetadata* SearchStruct) const
944 {
945 const FHashedName SearchName = SearchStruct->GetShaderVariableHashedName();
946
947 return GetUniformBufferParameter(SearchName);
948 }
949
950 /** Finds an automatically bound uniform buffer matching the HashedName if one exists, or returns an unbound parameter. */
951 FORCEINLINE_DEBUGGABLE const FShaderUniformBufferParameter& GetUniformBufferParameter(const FHashedName SearchName) const
952 {
953 int32 FoundIndex = INDEX_NONE;
954 TArrayView<const FHashedName> UniformBufferParameterStructsView(UniformBufferParameterStructs);
955 for (int32 StructIndex = 0, Count = UniformBufferParameterStructsView.Num(); StructIndex < Count; StructIndex++)
956 {
957 if (UniformBufferParameterStructsView[StructIndex] == SearchName)
958 {
959 FoundIndex = StructIndex;
960 break;
961 }
962 }
963
964 if (FoundIndex != INDEX_NONE)
965 {
966 const FShaderUniformBufferParameter& FoundParameter = UniformBufferParameters[FoundIndex];
967 return FoundParameter;
968 }
969 else
970 {
971 // This can happen if the uniform buffer was not bound
972 // There's no good way to distinguish not being bound due to temporary debugging / compiler optimizations or an actual code bug,
973 // Hence failing silently instead of an error message
974 static FShaderUniformBufferParameter UnboundParameter;
975 return UnboundParameter;
976 }
977 }

1223 template<typename ShaderType1>

1226 if (Lhs.GetShader() == Rhs.GetShader())
1227 {
1228 check(Lhs.GetShaderMap() == Rhs.GetShaderMap());
1229 return true;
1230 }
1231 return false;
1232 }
1233
1234 template<typename ShaderType1>
1235 friend inline bool operator!=(const TShaderRefBase& Lhs, const TShaderRefBase<ShaderType1, PointerTableType>& Rhs)
1236 {
1237 return !operator==(Lhs, Rhs);
1238 }
1239
1240};

1601inline FString LexToString(FShaderType::EShaderTypeForDynamicCast ShaderType)
1602{
1603#define SHADER_TYPE_ENTRY(Name) TEXT(#Name)
1604 static const TCHAR* TypeStrings[] =
1605 {
1606 SHADER_TYPE_LIST
1607 };
1608#undef SHADER_TYPE_ENTRY
1609 checkf(ShaderType < FShaderType::EShaderTypeForDynamicCast::NumShaderTypes, TEXT("Invalid shader type"));
1610 static_assert((sizeof(TypeStrings) / sizeof(TCHAR*)) == (int)FShaderType::EShaderTypeForDynamicCast::NumShaderTypes);
1611 return TypeStrings[static_cast<uint32>(ShaderType)];
1612}

1614/**
1615 * Registers a shader type in various systems. Should be created as a static field/global.
1616 *
1617 * Each shader type is collected here, not as an instance but as an accessor, so the actual construction can be deferred.
1618 * The collection happens during static init, the actual construction happens later during launch.
1619 * The purpose of collecting the types is the CommitAll function, called in LaunchEngineLoop, to ensure all type instances are constructed and registered before other systems start iterating them.
1620 */
1621class FShaderTypeRegistration
1622{
1623public:
1624 FShaderTypeRegistration(TFunctionRef<FShaderType& ()> LazyShaderTypeAccessor)
1625 : LazyShaderTypeAccessor(LazyShaderTypeAccessor)
1626 {
1627 GetInstances().Add(this);
1628 }
1629
1630 static RENDERCORE_API TArray<const FShaderTypeRegistration*>& GetInstances();
1631
1632 // Actually register all the types and clear the array
1633 static RENDERCORE_API void CommitAll();
1634
1635private:
1636 TFunctionRef<FShaderType& ()> LazyShaderTypeAccessor;
1637};

2193/** Used to compare two shader types by name. */
2194class FCompareShaderTypes
2195{
2196public:
2197 FORCEINLINE bool operator()(const FShaderType& A, const FShaderType& B ) const
2198 {
2199 int32 AL = FCString::Strlen(A.GetName());
2200 int32 BL = FCString::Strlen(B.GetName());
2201 if ( AL == BL )
2202 {
2203 return FCString::Strncmp(A.GetName(), B.GetName(), AL) > 0;
2204 }
2205 return AL > BL;
2206 }
